-----------------------------------------------------------------------
-                          QUICK REFERENCES                           -
-----------------------------------------------------------------------

new session => tmux new -s work
reattach session => tmux a -d

create window  => C-a c
close window => C-a &
list windows   => C-a w
rename current window => C-a ,
close current pane   => C-a x
toggle current pane zoom (used for copying stuff to system clipboard)=> C-a z
last window (used to toggle between two sessions)=> C-a l

-----------------------------------------------------------------------
-                          OTHER OPERATIONS                           -
-----------------------------------------------------------------------
1. copy txt from a pane to vim in a different pane
 * Ctrl + A Esc to enter copy mode
 * Move to start of txt
 * Hit v
 * select region, hit y to copy
 * go back to vim, enter insert mode
 * Ctrl + A p to paste
2. common copy mode shortcuts
 * Begin of line ^
 * End of line   $
 * Page down     Ctrl-d
 * Page up       Ctrl-u
